en_139366_0	Troops of the Security Forces Headquarters - Kilinochchi warmly welcomed the ‘Paada Yathra’ devotees when they arrived in Kilinochchi area during 4-5 August in order to attend the annual feast at Matha Church in Mulankavil on Sunday (4) before they set out to the Holy Shrine of Madu.
en_139366_1	On the directions of Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi, troops of 19 Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) and 11 (Volunteer) Gajaba Regiment extended their hospitality by providing refreshments to the those devotees on 'Paada Yathra'.
en_139366_2	On 5 August, the devotees were offered drinking water by the troops in the 651 Brigade near the Paliaru Bridge while they were walking towards the Madhu Church.
